<h1>Download page for McStas</h1>
<p>For specific installation instructions for your platform, please
consult the respective pages (Warning - McStas 2.1 and later):
<ul>
  <li><a href="install_linux/">Linux (and general Unix) Installation page</a>
  <li><a href="install_mac_os_x/">Mac OS X Installation page</a>
    <li><a href="install_windows/">Windows Installation page</a>
</ul>
  
<p>If you are on Unix (Linux/Mac) and want to keep your McStas 1.x or 2.0
alongside McStas 2.1, please use our migration scripts
<ul>
  <li><a target=_blank
  href="http://trac.mccode.org/browser/trunk/tools/migration-tool/migrate-mcstas-1.x.sh">mcstas
  1.x migration script</a>
  <li><a target=_blank
  href="http://trac.mccode.org/browser/trunk/tools/migration-tool/migrate-mcstas-2.0.sh">mcstas
  2.0 migration script</a>
</ul>

<b>BEFORE</b> attempting to installing McStas 2.1.

<p>Below, the distribution packages for McStas may be downloaded. Details
and important information about each release may be found <a href="CHANGES_McStas">here</a>. Please, also read <a href="../about/conditions">the conditions of use</a>
for McStas. <strong>For other user contributions, minor fixes to individual files,
please see our <a href="share/">share download</a> section.</strong>
McStas is available in source code form for Unix-like systems, as
well as precompiled versions for Windows, Linux and Mac OS X. The
new version has been tested on a variety of <a href="/developments/platforms">platforms</a>,
but should compile also for most other Unix systems. An ANSI-C compiler
is required; GCC works well.
In case of difficulties, contact the <a href="mailto:mcstas@risoe.dk">McStas
administrator</a> so that the problems may be solved in the next
version.<br>
</p><p>For support and usage, we encourage you to become a member of our
